All the programming projects that I'm doing with Cate, my daughter starting at 10 years old

social-drawing: 
  - A simple canvas to draw
  - A color palatte on top with 7 colors
    - she wants neon colo
  - Move the mouse
  - Click and move to draw
  - Bonus
    - a friend can join and draw on a shared canvas
  - reference: 
    - http://dev.opera.com/articles/view/html5-canvas-painting/


-------
Reference commands
  git config --global user.name "Tony Tam"
  git config --global user.name "tam.tony@gmail.com"
  git init
  git add README
  git commit -m 'first commit for social drawing' README
  git remote add origin https://tam.tony@code.google.com/p/teaching-kids-programming/ 
  git push -u origin master
